	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Columbia S. C.</placeName>&#44; <date>Sept 21&#44; &#39;52</date></p>
				<p><sic><addressee>Rev. Lesser Esq.</addressee></sic> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I herewith take the liberty to turn to<lb/> you with the request to send me the<lb/> Occident of which you are the editor.  At<lb/> the same time I want to tell you of the<lb/> condition in which our Community finds<lb/> itself.  We have a Hazan here.  But&#44; as<lb/> you know&#44; we have no Shohet.  Never&#45;<lb/>theless I have occasionally found<lb/> a seal &#34;Kosher&#34; on the meat.  With<lb/> regard to this I have naturally spoken<lb/> frequently.  The &#34;Yehudin&#34; here are&#44;<lb/> however&#44; such ignoramuses that they<lb/> are perfectly content if they see a seal<lb/> on the meat&#44; and do not bother to know<lb/> who <del>put</del> attached it&#44; whether a man<lb/> who knows anything about slaughtering<lb/> or not&#44; whether he has legal permission<lb/> <add>Kaballa</add> to slaughter&#44; or not.  To them<lb/> these things do not matter.  But it is</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>2</p>
				<p>wrong of a man who has no <hi rend="underline">Kaballa</hi><lb/> and knows nothing of Shehita&#44; to act as<lb/> Shohet for a community.  It is even worse<lb/> for a man who wants to live as a Jew<lb/> and is in this way deprived of the op&#45;<lb/>portunity.  For when we want to obtain<lb/> a pious Jew as Shohet&#44; he can find<lb/> no welcome here&#44; since people say<lb/> &#34;we obtain our meat properly slaughtered<lb/> and have no need for a shohet.&#34;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You must&#44; therefore&#44; agree with me<lb/> that a man such as this cannot be<lb/> called a Jew.  For whatever he may do<lb/> for himself&#44; to slaughter for a community<lb/> and to hang a seal on the meat so that<lb/> it might be sold as kosher&#44; is not<lb/> the work of an upright Jew.  Such action<lb/> is hypocrisy and pious swindle&#44;<lb/> as you must agree.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">That is why I turned to you&#44; and<lb/> am sending you one of the seals which<lb/> I <del>be</del> removed from the meat only this</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>3</p>
				<p>morning when I was in the market.<lb/>  I hope some good will come of your<lb/> making this matter public.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I shall be in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> in a<lb/> few weeks&#44; and shall at the same time<lb/> purchase several holiday prayer books from you<lb/> of which I have need.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In the hope that this letter will<lb/> find you in good health&#44; and<lb/> that you will send me the Occident&#44;<lb/> I remain<lb/> Your devoted friend&#44;</p>
				<p><persName role="author">L. Elias</persName></p>
				<p>Please send the Occident begin<lb/>ning with <date>Rosh ha&#45;Shana</date></p>
		</body>
